    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of  large tree native to the eastern United States and southeast Canada, growing up 27 meters tall and living to 200 years. Mature trees are recognized by their rough shinglelike bark; young trees have smooth bark.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
